<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1029,1595]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,356,1100,1127]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Remarks (1).</emphasis>
The alternating lifecycle was closed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[821,1123,1101,1127]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
and the asexual generation was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[351,553,1137,1163]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="812 - 830" refId="ref44445" refString="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y. (2016) First description of asexual generation and taxonomic revision of the gall wasp genus Latuspina (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 109 (5), 812 - 830. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / saw 051" type="journal article" year="2016">Ide &amp; Abe (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1029,1595]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,358,1172,1199]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Remarks (2).</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." box="[367,673,1173,1199]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
photographed the sexual gall and described it as ‘Kunugi-ha-urashiro-ke-tama-fushi’ (C-087), and the asexual gall as ‘Kunugi-ha-suji-ko-tama-fushi’ (C-082). Later, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="812 - 830" refId="ref44445" refString="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y. (2016) First description of asexual generation and taxonomic revision of the gall wasp genus Latuspina (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 109 (5), 812 - 830. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / saw 051" type="journal article" year="2016">Ide &amp; Abe (2016)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that these galls correspond to the sexual and asexual generations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ide &amp; Abe" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Ashmead" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[1112,1209,1246,1271]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Latuspina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nawai">
<emphasis box="[1112,1209,1246,1271]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">L. nawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref55993" refString="Yukawa, J. &amp; Masuda, H. (1996) Insect and mite galls of Japan in colors. Zenkoku-Nouson-Kyoukai, Tokyo, 826 pp. [in Japanese]" type="book" year="1996">Yukawa &amp; Masuda (1996)</bibRefCitation>
said also that galls C-091 and C-098 belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1904" box="[771,972,1282,1307]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Neuroterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nawai">
<emphasis box="[771,972,1282,1307]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Neuroterus nawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1904" box="[990,1089,1282,1307]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Neuroterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nawai">
<emphasis box="[990,1089,1282,1307]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">L. nawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); however, they correspond to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pujade-Villar &amp; Melika" authorityYear="2020" box="[151,524,1317,1343]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Cerroneuroterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yukawamasudai">
<emphasis box="[151,524,1317,1343]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Cerroneuroterus yukawamasudai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see Remarks for this species).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1029,1595]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,357,1352,1379]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Remarks (3).</emphasis>
The name ‘ 
<taxonomicName box="[497,761,1353,1379]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Cerroneuroterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nawai">
<emphasis box="[497,761,1353,1379]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Cerroneuroterus nawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ was mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation author="Melika, G. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Bihari, P. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z." box="[990,1223,1353,1379]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="143 - 163" refId="ref48306" refString="Melika, G., Tang, C. - T., Yang, M. - M., Bihari, P., Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z. (2012) New species of cynipid inquilines of the genus Ufo Melika &amp; Pujade-Villar, 2005 (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini). Zootaxa, 3478 (1), 143 - 163. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3478.1.17" type="journal article" year="2012">
Melika 
<emphasis box="[1078,1137,1353,1379]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al.</emphasis>
(2012)
</bibRefCitation>
, but this combination has never been formally published. Furthermore, the galls of this species, which appeared also in 
<bibRefCitation author="Melika, G. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Abe, Y. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Nicholls, J. &amp; Wachi, N. &amp; Ide, T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Penzes, Zs &amp; Csoka, G. &amp; Stone, G. N." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1 - 79" refId="ref47700" refString="Melika, G., Pujade-Villar, J., Abe, Y., Tang, C. - T., Nicholls, J., Wachi, N., Ide, T., Yang, M. - M., Penzes, Zs, Csoka, G. &amp; Stone, G. N. (2010) Palaearctic oak gallwasps galling oaks (Quercus) in the section Cerris: re-appraisal of generic limits, with descriptions of new genera and species (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Zootaxa, 2470 (1), 1 - 79. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2470.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">
Melika 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,1389,1415]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName box="[263,364,1426,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Cerroneuroterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nawai">
<emphasis box="[263,364,1426,1451]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">N. nawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, actually correspond to the asexual form of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pujade-Villar &amp; Melika" authorityYear="2020" box="[858,1071,1425,1451]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Cerroneuroterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yukawamasudai">
<emphasis box="[858,1071,1425,1451]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">C. yukawamasudai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1029,1595]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1460,1487]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Remarks (4).</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Kang, M. &amp; Bae, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Roca-Cusachs, M. &amp; Jung, S." box="[359,661,1461,1487]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1208 - 1221" refId="ref50634" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Kang, M., Bae, J., Wang, Y., Guo, R., Roca-Cusachs, M. &amp; Jung, S. (2020 a) Current state of knowledge of the Korean Cynipini: Subspecies description, new combinations and checklist (Hymenoptera, Cynipidae). Journal of AsiaPacific Entomology, 23 (4), 1208 - 1221. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. aspen. 2020.08.012" type="journal article" year="2020">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[514,561,1461,1487]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">et al</emphasis>
. (2020a)
</bibRefCitation>
placed 
<taxonomicName box="[745,844,1462,1487]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Cerroneuroterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nawai">
<emphasis box="[745,844,1462,1487]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">N. nawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<emphasis box="[879,1088,1461,1487]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">species inquirenda</emphasis>
, but it had already been revised and transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Monzen" authorityYear="1954" box="[356,468,1498,1523]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Latuspina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[356,468,1498,1523]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Latuspina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y." box="[510,711,1497,1523]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="812 - 830" refId="ref44445" refString="Ide, T. &amp; Abe, Y. (2016) First description of asexual generation and taxonomic revision of the gall wasp genus Latuspina (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Cynipini). Annals of the Entomological Society of America, 109 (5), 812 - 830. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / aesa / saw 051" type="journal article" year="2016">Ide &amp; Abe (2016)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,1029,1595]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1533,1559]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Biology.</emphasis>
Both generations induce detachable leaf galls on 
<taxonomicName box="[853,1007,1533,1559]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="acutissima">
<emphasis box="[853,1007,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Q. acutissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1061,1203,1533,1559]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variabilis">
<emphasis box="[1061,1203,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Q. variabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[1277,1349,1533,1559]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cerris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1277,1349,1533,1559]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Cerris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (Table 1; 
